    "what_description": "Polystichum rhizophorum is a species of fern in the family Polypodiaceae. It is a terrestrial fern with a rhizome that produces long, creeping stems bearing pinnately compound fronds, typically 15-40 cm in length. The fronds have 10-20 pairs of lanceolate to ovate pinnae, which are serrated at the margins. The plant reproduces via spores produced on the underside of the pinnae, which are yellowish-brown in color, and via the production of new plants from the tips of the rhizome, a process known as stoloniferous reproduction. Polystichum rhizophorum is native to the tropical regions of Central and South America.",
