    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Polystichum rhizophorum are derived from its leaves and roots, with varying solvents and methods used to extract its bioactive compounds. Tea is prepared by infusing dried leaves in hot water, typically used for its diuretic and antiseptic properties. Infusion involves steeping fresh or dried leaves in cold water for a longer period, often used for its antioxidant and anti-inflammatory effects. A tincture is made by soaking the plant material in a solvent like ethanol or glycerin, commonly used for its adaptogenic and anti-stress properties. Polystichum decoction, a concentrated liquid extract, and salve, a topical application of the plant's oil or extract, are also used to leverage the plant's potential therapeutic benefits.",
